    "), to date only a small percentage of manufacturers have considered deploying AI and other Industrie 4.0 technologies within their operations.For the small percentage of companies equipped to consider advanced technology offerings, there is a further challenge.",
    "Challenge 2: AI and other Industries 4.0 technologies don't directly match industrial needs.Those technologies associated with the 3rd Industrial Revolution were designed to be a direct match for computing challenges at different levels of factory operations; the same cannot be said for those linked to the 4th Industrial Revolution.",
    "Referring to Fig. 1 these \"floating\" technologies can potentially apply as part of many different digital solutions and there is no one-to-one match between 4th Industrial Revolution technologies and industrial operational levels.",
    "Further, these technologies rarely present as complete solutions to an industrial need.",
    "Machine learning software for example might be part of any of a number of solutions (e.g., feedback control, quality inspection, schedule optimization)-but importantly, only part."
